cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of inferring 3D spatial occupancy of objects from 2D image detections, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a robust regularization method and a robust ellipse fitting algorithm, which are related to machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also involves algebraic solutions and geometric reasoning, which are related to artificial intelligence and computational geometry, respectively. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics) are also possible categories.
